## Issue 1 — Add ADF lags to the SADF specification (methodological fix)

The current SADF implementation fits a simple regression `Δy_t = α + β·y_{t−1} + ε_t` with zero augmentation lags. AFML §17.4.2.6 (Snippet 17.1) shows that the SADF inner loop should accept a `lags` parameter and include lagged `Δy` terms in the design matrix to absorb serial correlation in the residuals. Without lags, the t-statistic can be inflated in the presence of autocorrelated errors.

**Required changes:**
- Add an optional `lags: int = 1` parameter to `compute_sadf_signal`.
- Augment the design matrix inside the inner loop to include `lags` columns of lagged `Δy`.
- Adjust the normal equation accumulators (`XtX`, `Xty`) and degrees of freedom accordingly.
- Update the docstring to document the new parameter.

