Both `compute_sadf_signal` and `compute_smt_signal` have tight double `for` loops in pure Python/NumPy that will be impractically slow on production-length series (thousands to tens of thousands of bars). AFML §17.4.2.2 explicitly discusses the heavy computational cost of SADF.

**Required changes:**
- Extract the core double-loop logic of each function into a helper decorated with `@numba.njit`.
- Replace `np.linalg.pinv(XtX)` in the SADF loop with the analytical closed-form inverse of a 2×2 matrix: swap diagonals, negate off-diagonals, divide by determinant. This avoids calling a LAPACK routine inside a JIT-compiled function.
- Keep the outer wrapper functions (with pandas I/O and logging) unchanged; only the inner numerical kernel needs to be JIT-compiled.
- Add `import numba` at the top of the module.

